A state judge has ruled that the Florida secretary of state may ignore

vote results submitted after the 5 p.m. ET deadline, but must consider all

appropriate circumstances -- in effect, leaving the final decision on the

state recounts up to the Florida secretary of state.


Go to ABCNEWS.com for the latest developments on the crucial Florida

recount.


http://www.abcnews.go.com


